documentation.text: Interface for the FakeproposalHandler

@dev getPrice() returns the price of an NFT from the FakeproposalHandler
 @return Returns the price in Wei for an NFT

@dev available() returns whether or not the given _tokenId has already been purchased
 @return Returns a boolean value - true if available, false if not

@dev purchase() purchases an NFT from the FakeproposalHandler
 @param _tokenId - the fake NFT tokenID to purchase

Minimal interface for stuNFT containing only two functions
 that we are interested in

@dev executeProposal allows any stuNFT holder to execute a proposal after it's deadline has been exceeded
 @param proposalIndex - the index of the proposal to execute in the proposals array
@dev withdrawEther allows the contract owner (deployer) to withdraw the ETH from the contract
Interface for the FakeproposalHandler

@dev getPrice() returns the price of an NFT from the FakeproposalHandler
 @return Returns the price in Wei for an NFT

@dev available() returns whether or not the given _tokenId has already been purchased
 @return Returns a boolean value - true if available, false if not

@dev purchase() purchases an NFT from the FakeproposalHandler
 @param _tokenId - the fake NFT tokenID to purchase

Minimal interface for stuNFT containing only two functions
 that we are interested in

@dev executeProposal allows any stuNFT holder to execute a proposal after it's deadline has been exceeded
 @param proposalIndex - the index of the proposal to execute in the proposals array
@dev withdrawEther allows the contract owner (deployer) to withdraw the ETH from the contract

createProposal(uint256).details: createProposal allows a stuNFT holder to create a new proposal in the DAO

params._nftTokenId: - the tokenID of the NFT to be purchased from FakeproposalHandler if this proposal passes

returns._0: Returns the proposal index for the newly created proposal

executeProposal(uint256).details: executeProposal allows any stuNFT holder to execute a proposal after it's deadline has been exceeded

params.proposalIndex: - the index of the proposal to execute in the proposals array

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

voteOnProposal(uint256,uint8).details: voteOnProposal allows a stuNFT holder to cast their vote on an active proposal

params.proposalIndex: - the index of the proposal to vote on in the proposals array
params.vote: - the type of vote they want to cast

withdrawEther().details: withdrawEther allows the contract owner (deployer) to withdraw the ETH from the contract
